The Odia database name as SITB-OSED is created by the Silicon Institute of Technology, Bhubaneswar, India. The database contains 12 professional 
speakers(6 males and 6 females) who participated in data recording. In total, the database contains 7317 utterances in different dialects of the 
Odia language. The SITB-OSED database comprises the basics of six emotions: 1) Anger 2) Surprise 3) Happy 4) Sadness 5) Disgust 6) Fear. The duration 
of the utterances was vary between 3.5s to 8s. All the samples were recorded in .wav format and 16-bit quantization rate with a sample rate of 22050 Hz.

We are releasing the database very soon!!
